## Open-source governance must separate project code from source data

Use **Apache-2.0** for code and optionally **CC BY 4.0** for original documentation. Source datasets do not inherit the project license. Maintain a dedicated `DATA_SOURCES.md` that records each source URL, terms, attribution, redistribution status, snapshot digest, and update date.

CDE's copyright statement says that, unless otherwise noted, reproducing website material generally requires permission. CDE marks and seals also must not be used as project branding. The first release should therefore:

- avoid committing large raw files to Git;
- avoid applying the project license to CDE source data;
- retrieve sources from official locations and publish reviewed factual derivatives only after terms are confirmed;
- avoid CDE seals and any claim of official endorsement;
- preserve source, version, method, and correction links on every relevant page.

The repository should contain the web application, data pipeline, data contracts, fixtures, tests, architecture decisions, workflows, methodology, contribution guide, code of conduct, security policy, and versioned data changelog.

References: [CDE Copyright Statement](https://www.cde.ca.gov/RE/di/cr/index.asp) and [CDE Web Policy](https://www.cde.ca.gov/re/di/ws/webpolicy.asp)
